    <section>
      <div class="section-title">❓ Frequently Asked Questions</div>
      <p><strong>Can I study if I am on benefits?</strong><br />Yes. Being on benefits does not prevent you from studying or receiving student finance.</p>
      <p><strong>Do I need to pay back student finance?</strong><br />You only repay if you earn over £30,000/year.</p>
      <p><strong>Can I study while working?</strong><br />Yes! The flexible timetable is designed for working adults.</p>
      <p><strong>What if I haven’t studied in years?</strong><br />We support all students, even those returning after a long gap.</p>
      <p><strong>Do I need formal qualifications?</strong><br />No. Life or work experience is accepted in many cases.</p>
      <p><strong>What support do you offer?</strong><br />From application to finance and even assignments — we’re with you all the way.</p>
